1. Purpose

The Audience Matrix v1.2 provides the canonical ruleset that governs all audience-dependent behaviors within Prospera OS.
It determines allowable actions, capability boundaries, fallback paths, routing constraints, escalation behavior, and constitutional limitations across all subsystems.

The matrix is the authoritative source for:

• generation constraints
• execution boundaries
• routing permissions
• safety enforcement
• system behavior consistency
• audience risk governance

────────────────────────────────────────

2. Scope

Included:

• full matrix structure (classes × subsystems)
• matrix cell decision rules
• capability tier enforcement
• fallback and downgrade rules
• escalation and block conditions
• constitutional override conditions

Excluded:

• state machine logic (defined separately)
• predictive calculations (PO2 handles scoring)
• module-level stylistic or UI rules

────────────────────────────────────────

3. Matrix Structure (v1.2)

The Audience Matrix is a 4 × 12 deterministic decision grid:

Audience Classes

• Class A
• Class B
• Class C
• Class D (Constitutional Boundary Class)

Subsystems

• Identity
• Intent
• Modeling
• Memory
• Safety
• Generation
• Execution
• Backtracking
• Recovery
• Autonomy
• Routing
• Pipeline

Each matrix cell maps to one decision:

ALLOW | RESTRICT | DOWNGRADE | BLOCK


All matrix evaluations must be deterministic and reproducible.

