5. Matrix Decision Rules (v1.2)
5.1 Class A Rules (High Trust)
Always ALLOW unless:
• constitutional boundary triggered → DOWNGRADE
• subsystem is privileged (Pipeline/Autonomy) → RESTRICT


Notes:

• Class A may not bypass Safety System
• Privileged calls require Envelope PASS

5.2 Class B Rules (Standard Controlled)
ALLOW for:
• Intent
• Identity
• Modeling
• Execution
• Generation

RESTRICT for:
• Pipeline
• Routing (requires capability check)

DOWNGRADE for:
• Autonomy (default)

5.3 Class C Rules (Restricted)
RESTRICT for all non-privileged subsystems

DOWNGRADE for:
• Generation
• Execution
• Modeling

BLOCK for:
• Pipeline
• Autonomy
• Recovery
• Backtracking

5.4 Class D Rules (Constitutional Boundary Class)
BLOCK everything except:
• Identity System
• Safety System


Additional constraints:

• All actions require constitutional audit
• No routing transitions allowed
• No execution/generation operations permitted

