6. Capability Tier Enforcement

Each audience class maps to a capability tier:

Class A → Tier A  
Class B → Tier B  
Class C → Tier C  
Class D → Tier D  


Tier rules:

• subsystem calls may not exceed audience tier
• downgrade is mandatory if risk ≥ threshold
• Safety System must verify tier alignment

────────────────────────────────────────

7. Fallback & Downgrade Rules

Fallback is used when:

• predictive risk (PO2) ≥ medium
• subsystem requirements exceed capability tier
• governance flags mismatch
• prohibited transitions detected

Fallback mapping:

ALLOW → RESTRICT  
RESTRICT → DOWNGRADE  
DOWNGRADE → BLOCK  
BLOCK → Kernel Arbitration only


All fallbacks must be recorded in lineage.

────────────────────────────────────────

8. Escalation Rules

Escalation is triggered when:

• constitutional restrictions apply
• Envelope v2.0 prohibits intended action
• subsystem privilege violation
• predictive anomaly score ≥ critical threshold

Escalation results:

Class A → Class B
Class B → Class C
Class C → Class D
Class D → Hold (governance review)


Escalations are irreversible within the same operation.

